The Benin Bronzes are a collection of over 900 bronze sculptures and terra cotta plaques that were looted from the Kingdom of Benin in 1897 by British soldiers. The Benin Bronzes were returned to the country in 2018, and the Benin Dialogue Group was formed to help the country develop a plan for the repatriation of the Benin Bronzes and other cultural artifacts.

The Benin Dialogue Group is a group of 15 people from the United Kingdom and Nigeria. The group is made up of 10 members from the United Kingdom and five members from Nigeria. The group was formed in 2018 and is chaired by the British Museum. The group is tasked with developing a plan for the repatriation of the Benin Bronzes and other cultural artifacts to Nigeria.
